Re: Could the bitcoin network be destroyed by someone generating endless
bitcoin add

Bitcointalk

2010-05-16 21:01:44 UTC - [11]Original Post

   When you generate a new bitcoin address, it only takes disk space on
   your own computer (like 500 bytes).  Itʼs like generating a new PGP
   private key, but less CPU intensive because itʼs ECC.  The address
   space is effectively unlimited.  It doesnʼt hurt anyone, so generate
   all you want.
